  "preparation": "Your bowel needs to be completely empty and clean for the exam. You need to drink plenty of clear liquids for 1 to 3 days before the test.",
  "howPerformed": "The scope is gently inserted through the anus. It is carefully moved into the lowest part of the large intestine.",
  "followup": "You should be able to return to your regular activities the next day. Avoid driving, operating machinery, drinking alcohol, and making important decisions for at least 24 hours.",
